<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="49" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1158,1759]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,313,1663,1687]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[585,739,1662,1687]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Parallygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="divaricatus">
<emphasis box="[585,739,1662,1687]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">P. divaricatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but can be distinguished from the latter by the dorsal pygofer processes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[197,1042,1734,1759]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1158,1759]" box="[197,1042,1734,1759]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,331,1735,1759]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Etymology.</emphasis>
